title: Real Foods Recalls Chicken Wrap Products Due To Misbranding And Undeclared Allergen
summary: WASHINGTON, Aug. 28, 2015 Real Foods, a Kent, Wash. establishment, is recalling approximately 41 pounds of chicken wrap products due to misbranding and an undeclared allergen, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
